explanation: This solution uses a depth-first search (DFS) to generate a De Bruijn sequence, which is a cyclic sequence that contains every possible substring of length n. The key insight is that the De Bruijn sequence can be constructed by iteratively appending a digit to the current sequence, ensuring that the resulting sequence has not been visited before. The use of an unordered set to keep track of visited sequences allows for efficient lookups and prevents revisiting the same sequence.

